* Install R
1. Download the most recent version of R.
2. Start the R program; 
3. As a first step with R, start the R help browser by typing help.start() in the R command window. For help on any function, e.g. the “mean” function, type ? mean.

Then, users can install Xtail from source package or binary package:
* Install source package
Download the source package from "packages" directory, e.g. xtail_1.1.2-source.tar.gz;
For Windows:
Before install, you need install "Rtools", "MainGW";     
Then using the following command to install: install.packages("xtail_1.1.2-source.tar.gz",repo=NULL,type="source")
For Linux or Mac:
install.package("xtail_1.1.2-source.tar.gz")

*  Installing binary package
Download the binary package from "packages" directory, e.g. xtail_1.1.2-windows.tar.gz; 
For windows and Mac, users can install Xtail using R's package installer
For linux, type the following in an R command window: install.package("xtail_1.1.2-linux.tar.gz")
